01:43:22.817 --> 01:43:25.598
You think
I'd contaminate myself?

01:43:25.632 --> 01:43:28.730
I think you'd do anything
to hurt this company.

01:43:31.775 --> 01:43:33.717
- Then I spilled it.
- What?

01:43:33.759 --> 01:43:35.963
I spilled
my urine sample container.

01:43:36.000 --> 01:43:39.032
Somebody must have put
plutonium in my container.

01:43:39.071 --> 01:43:41.887
And then I spilled it
on my bathroom floor.

01:43:41.920 --> 01:43:46.326
I cleaned it all up
and my hands must have got hot.

01:43:46.367 --> 01:43:48.735
And then what did I touch?

01:43:48.767 --> 01:43:50.654
OK, I touched my sink...

01:43:50.686 --> 01:43:54.003
I touched my make-up...

01:43:54.047 --> 01:43:57.843
and I forget what stuff
in the refrigerator.

01:43:57.886 --> 01:44:01.683
That's it. See?

01:44:01.726 --> 01:44:03.614
Somebody spiked
my urine sample container.

01:44:03.647 --> 01:44:05.435
- Who?
- Boy!

01:44:05.470 --> 01:44:08.055
How do I know who?
Anybody could have done it.

01:44:08.094 --> 01:44:11.389
You leave it sitting there by
the punch-in at the plant!

01:44:11.422 --> 01:44:15.676
Anybody could've dropped
a little plutonium in there.

01:44:15.709 --> 01:44:18.906
There's a lot of people
at the plant hate me.

01:44:18.941 --> 01:44:21.843
The whole house is hot.
How did it get hot?

01:44:21.886 --> 01:44:23.773
I spilled it!
I told you, man!

01:44:23.806 --> 01:44:25.213
That doesn't explain
the readings...

01:44:25.245 --> 01:44:27.317
we're getting
on your nasal smear.

01:44:27.356 --> 01:44:29.528
45,000 DPM.

01:44:32.061 --> 01:44:33.467
What?

01:44:33.500 --> 01:44:35.410
45,000 DPM.

01:44:36.381 --> 01:44:37.941
Oh, my Jesus.

01:44:39.740 --> 01:44:44.180
I'm internally contaminated.
That's what you mean.

01:44:44.220 --> 01:44:45.464
We don't know what it means.

01:44:45.499 --> 01:44:47.987
- That's what you mean!
- Karen, calm down.

01:44:52.699 --> 01:44:54.740
Karen, listen.

01:44:54.781 --> 01:44:56.918
Get out of my way!

01:45:01.147 --> 01:45:05.172
Oh, Jesus!
Where am I going to go now?

01:45:05.211 --> 01:45:07.545
I don't have anyplace to go now.

01:45:07.579 --> 01:45:10.840
We're getting a room for Dolly.
We want to help you.

01:45:10.874 --> 01:45:12.817
We can help you
with a place to stay.

01:45:12.859 --> 01:45:14.452
We can help you with money.

01:45:26.234 --> 01:45:30.163
But first I have
to sign something, right?

01:45:30.202 --> 01:45:34.740
You want me to sign a statement
saying I did all this.

01:45:34.778 --> 01:45:37.745
Just in your own words
what happened.

01:45:44.153 --> 01:45:45.908
OK.

01:45:53.591 --> 01:45:56.178
In my own words?

01:45:58.232 --> 01:46:00.142
I'm contaminated.

01:46:01.880 --> 01:46:03.789
I'm dying.

01:48:48.047 --> 01:48:50.121
What are you doing here?

01:48:50.160 --> 01:48:54.284
I'm just looking around,
like you.

01:49:58.764 --> 01:50:00.706
You're here.

01:50:00.748 --> 01:50:03.978
Jesus Christ.
I didn't know where you were.

01:50:05.932 --> 01:50:07.938
What the hell happened?

01:50:13.003 --> 01:50:14.825
They're killing me.

01:50:14.859 --> 01:50:16.168
They're trying to kill me.

01:50:16.204 --> 01:50:19.072
They want me
to stop what I'm doing.

01:50:19.114 --> 01:50:22.660
They contaminated me,
you know that?

01:50:22.699 --> 01:50:25.219
I'm internally contaminated now.

01:50:26.986 --> 01:50:29.092
Now, you listen to me.

01:50:29.131 --> 01:50:32.000
We're going to go
to Los Alamos on Thursday...

01:50:32.042 --> 01:50:33.929
and we'll get a full body count
from some doctors...

01:50:33.962 --> 01:50:35.620
who know what they're doing.
All three of us.

01:50:35.659 --> 01:50:39.237
Oh, God! I'm so scared now.

01:51:00.809 --> 01:51:03.526
It says here that
there's plutonium missing...

01:51:03.561 --> 01:51:06.855
from just about every
nuclear plant in this country.

01:51:06.888 --> 01:51:10.019
- Who's got it?
- Any asshole that wants it.

01:51:10.057 --> 01:51:12.129
Man.

01:51:12.169 --> 01:51:16.063
That's the guy, Drew.

01:51:16.105 --> 01:51:17.827
The guy
Paul is bringing to see me.

01:51:17.864 --> 01:51:19.293
Who?

01:51:19.336 --> 01:51:21.638
The guy that wrote it,
from the "New York Times."

01:51:21.672 --> 01:51:23.265
If you're going to be
in the newspaper...

01:51:23.305 --> 01:51:25.508
I want to be in there, too.

01:51:32.391 --> 01:51:35.740
Dolly, did you...

01:51:35.783 --> 01:51:40.039
Did you tell the company
about the "New York Times"?

01:51:40.071 --> 01:51:42.144
No. I don't think
I remembered that part.

01:51:49.542 --> 01:51:51.998
Did you tell them
about the X-rays?

01:51:54.950 --> 01:51:58.016
- Dolly?
- No.

01:51:58.054 --> 01:52:00.094
Are you sure?

01:52:00.135 --> 01:52:03.483
Karen, they know
everything about us.

01:52:12.037 --> 01:52:14.623
They don't know
about the X-rays, do they?

01:52:51.651 --> 01:52:54.369
OK. That's it.

01:53:21.601 --> 01:53:25.016
All right, Mr. Stephens
and Miss Pelliker...

01:53:25.058 --> 01:53:29.019
you both check out well below
permissible body limits.

01:53:29.058 --> 01:53:31.610
You were exposed to
Miss Silkwood and the house...

01:53:31.649 --> 01:53:35.391
but you show minimum
detectable activity now.

01:53:37.665 --> 01:53:39.901
Miss Silkwood.

01:53:43.553 --> 01:53:47.579
We have detected
americium in both lungs...

01:53:47.617 --> 01:53:49.340
and both sides of your chest.

01:53:49.376 --> 01:53:52.637
Americium is produced
when plutonium disintegrates.

01:53:52.672 --> 01:53:55.192
And extrapolating from
your americium level...

01:53:55.233 --> 01:53:58.014
we estimate you have
an internal contamination...

01:53:58.048 --> 01:54:01.364
of six nanocuries of plutonium.

01:54:01.407 --> 01:54:03.611
The maximum permissible
body burden...

01:54:03.648 --> 01:54:07.096
for occupational exposure
is 40 nanocuries.

01:54:07.136 --> 01:54:10.332
As you can see,
you are well under that level.

01:54:10.367 --> 01:54:15.123
- I'm under it.
- As well as we can determine.

01:54:15.166 --> 01:54:18.266
These are very sophisticated
instruments...

01:54:18.304 --> 01:54:20.888
but their accuracy may be off...

01:54:20.927 --> 01:54:24.058
by plus or minus 300%
at this level.

01:54:25.567 --> 01:54:27.508
Plus or minus 300%?

01:54:27.550 --> 01:54:29.045
That's correct.

01:54:29.086 --> 01:54:31.290
Then what you're saying is...

01:54:31.326 --> 01:54:33.333
that the amount
of plutonium inside me...

01:54:33.374 --> 01:54:36.474
could be three times less
than you even think?

01:54:36.511 --> 01:54:39.161
Or three times greater.

01:54:40.925 --> 01:54:45.595
But even that would be under
the maximum body burden.

01:54:57.917 --> 01:55:01.463
I think you should come on
down to Oklahoma City...

01:55:01.501 --> 01:55:03.922
and bring that reporter
from the "New York Times."

01:55:03.964 --> 01:55:06.899
Are you ready to see him?

01:55:06.940 --> 01:55:08.347
I'm ready.

01:55:08.381 --> 01:55:10.322
You got the documents?

01:55:12.061 --> 01:55:13.434
Come on down.

01:55:17.851 --> 01:55:22.423
Man, I love it here.
I love this country.

01:55:22.459 --> 01:55:24.980
Wouldn't you like
to stay here forever?

01:55:27.963 --> 01:55:30.451
Doctors are all goddamn liars.

01:55:33.563 --> 01:55:36.694
Land's cheap there.

01:55:36.732 --> 01:55:39.098
I read about this.

01:55:39.130 --> 01:55:41.170
You can build yourself
a pueblo house.

01:55:42.235 --> 01:55:45.618
Make it out of adobe brick,
like the Indians.

01:55:45.659 --> 01:55:50.579
Mud, straw...
comes right out of the ground.

01:55:50.618 --> 01:55:53.520
Got to build a well,
but that's not too bad.

01:55:53.561 --> 01:55:56.017
You get a bunch of guys
to do you a favor.

01:55:56.058 --> 01:55:57.367
You do them a favor.

01:55:57.401 --> 01:55:59.889
It's all barter system
out there.

01:55:59.929 --> 01:56:01.718
You can make the rooms
any shape.

01:56:01.753 --> 01:56:03.160
You can make 'em round.

01:56:03.194 --> 01:56:04.982
It's not a right-angle
kind of life.

01:56:05.017 --> 01:56:06.392
Yeah.

01:56:08.313 --> 01:56:10.702
Have room for your kids.

01:56:13.273 --> 01:56:14.702
Yeah.

01:56:17.912 --> 01:56:20.051
Hell, we could have
kids of our own.

01:56:22.968 --> 01:56:24.878
We love each other.

01:56:31.352 --> 01:56:33.108
Why not?

01:56:38.232 --> 01:56:40.435
They wouldn't...

01:56:40.471 --> 01:56:42.839
They wouldn't come out right.

01:56:42.872 --> 01:56:45.238
Hell, I didn't come out right.

01:56:45.271 --> 01:56:47.181
You came out OK.

01:56:59.606 --> 01:57:01.516
What is it?

01:57:02.967 --> 01:57:04.876
Come on.

01:57:05.847 --> 01:57:09.360
Come on. I don't care.

01:57:10.806 --> 01:57:12.235
I know.

01:57:15.094 --> 01:57:16.753
You aren't going
to contaminate me...

01:57:16.789 --> 01:57:19.474
any more than
I've already been.

01:57:38.197 --> 01:57:40.946
I'm sorry.
I forgot to turn off the alarm.

01:57:43.765 --> 01:57:46.065
I thought you weren't going in.

01:57:46.100 --> 01:57:49.678
Well... I have to.

01:57:51.860 --> 01:57:53.747
Call in sick.

01:57:53.779 --> 01:57:55.668
No, I really do.

01:57:55.700 --> 01:57:58.733
I really mean
you ought to call in sick.

01:57:58.771 --> 01:58:00.876
Think they'll let you work?

01:58:00.915 --> 01:58:02.378
There's something I got to get.

01:58:02.420 --> 01:58:05.266
At the plant?
Are you wearing my shirt?

01:58:05.299 --> 01:58:06.860
- Huh?
- My shirt!

01:58:06.899 --> 01:58:10.248
You don't have to get up now.

01:58:10.291 --> 01:58:13.422
Sweetheart, don't go try get
anything out of the plant.

01:58:13.459 --> 01:58:15.183
If I get hung up
at the union meeting...

01:58:15.219 --> 01:58:16.910
will you pick up
Paul Stone and the guy...

01:58:16.946 --> 01:58:18.539
from the "New York Times"
at the airport?

01:58:18.579 --> 01:58:20.139
Fuck no.

01:58:20.179 --> 01:58:21.586
Come on, darling.

01:58:21.619 --> 01:58:23.025
I don't know how late
this meeting will go tonight.

01:58:23.059 --> 01:58:24.368
I don't want you doing that.

01:58:24.402 --> 01:58:27.664
Well... I'm doing it.

01:58:27.699 --> 01:58:30.065
You don't owe
the union anything.

01:58:30.097 --> 01:58:31.920
Let's not fight.

01:58:31.954 --> 01:58:34.441
You don't owe
the "New York Times" anything.

01:58:34.481 --> 01:58:37.230
Let's not have a fight now.

01:58:45.457 --> 01:58:47.367
We always can have a fight later.

01:59:15.376 --> 01:59:21.159
Amazing grace

01:59:21.200 --> 01:59:27.081
How sweet the sound

01:59:27.120 --> 01:59:31.788
That saved a wretch...

01:59:31.822 --> 01:59:35.619
- Give me your notes.
- OK.

01:59:35.662 --> 01:59:37.637
Listen, you sure you're OK?

01:59:37.679 --> 01:59:38.956
I'm OK.

01:59:38.991 --> 01:59:40.300
- Bye-bye!
- Bye.

01:59:40.335 --> 01:59:43.498
Once was lost

01:59:43.534 --> 01:59:49.099
But now I'm found

01:59:49.134 --> 01:59:51.949
Was blind

01:59:51.982 --> 01:59:59.434
But now I see

02:00:00.941 --> 02:00:06.309
'Twas grace that taught

02:00:06.349 --> 02:00:11.499
My heart to fear

02:00:11.533 --> 02:00:21.321
And grace my fears released

02:00:21.357 --> 02:00:31.721
How precious
did that grace appear

02:00:31.756 --> 02:00:41.826
The hour I first believed

02:00:41.867 --> 02:00:51.425
Through many dangers,
toils, and snares

02:00:51.467 --> 02:01:01.669
We have already come

02:01:01.706 --> 02:01:12.071
'Twas grace that brought us
safe thus far

02:01:12.107 --> 02:01:21.118
And grace will lead us home

02:01:21.160 --> 02:01:31.014
When we've been there
ten thousand years

02:01:31.050 --> 02:01:41.022
Bright-shining as the sun

02:01:41.064 --> 02:01:46.399
We've no less days

02:01:46.440 --> 02:01:51.622
To sing God's praise

02:01:51.656 --> 02:02:01.508
As when we first begun

02:02:01.543 --> 02:02:06.300
Amazing grace

02:02:06.343 --> 02:02:11.710
How sweet the sound

02:02:11.751 --> 02:02:21.571
That saved a wretch like me

02:02:21.606 --> 02:02:26.210
I once was lost

02:02:26.245 --> 02:02:31.331
But now I'm found

02:02:31.366 --> 02:02:38.043
Was bound, but now I'm free

